descript.abstract:
This polygon dataset shows the New Hampshire House of Representatives "floterial" district boundaries drawn by the New Hampshire Legislature based on the 2010 US Census population count.
Floterial districts overlay other NH House of Representatives districts ("base" districts), which are available from companion shape file NHHouseDistricts12. Both shape files are required to depict all NH House of Representatives districts. District boundaries were derived by applying district codes retrieved from the NH Secretary of State web site to the geometry provided by the GRANIT town boundary layer (PBNH).
descript.purpose: This dataset is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

attracc.attraccr: Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data. However, when information is missing or ambiguous, the GIS Information Systems Center at Tufts University researches other metadata sources for explanations. If sufficient information is unavailable, "unknown attribute" is given as the definition. If the attribute has been created through a geoprocessing function, "geoprocessed identifier" is given. If the attribute is known, but the values are not, "unknown" is given for values. Features' units of measurement are determined if not already given.

srcinfo.srccontr: Provided the listing of towns in each of NH State Representative base districts.

procstep.procdesc: Attribute was added to PBNH to capture the NH House of Representatives corresponding floterial district, if one existed, for each town. Areas with no floterial district were assigned no district code. For sub-municipal districts, ward boundary maps and descriptions were obtained from city offices. Boundaries were obtained from corresponding GRANIT base map layers (DOTRDS, NHHYDRO) and used to split municipalities into ward polygons. TOWNLISTINGS was used to populate the field. Results were "dissolved" to generate the House floterial district boundaries.
